#: ../../source/user_guide/feature_guide/cpu_binding.md:1
msgid "CPU Binding"
msgstr "CPU 绑定"

#: ../../source/user_guide/feature_guide/cpu_binding.md:3
msgid ""
"**Starting from vllm-ascend v0.18.0rc1, CPU binding is enabled by default"
" on ARM-based Ascend servers.**"
msgstr "**从 vllm-ascend v0.18.0rc1 开始，CPU 绑定在基于 ARM 的昇腾服务器上默认启用。**"

#: ../../source/user_guide/feature_guide/cpu_binding.md:6
msgid ""
"**You usually do not need to configure it manually.** Set "
"`enable_cpu_binding` only when you want to disable it or make the default"
" explicit."
msgstr "**通常您无需手动配置。** 仅当您想禁用它或明确默认行为时，才设置 `enable_cpu_binding`。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/feature_guide/cpu_binding.md:9
msgid "Benefits of CPU Binding"
msgstr "CPU 绑定的优势"

#: ../../source/user_guide/feature_guide/cpu_binding.md:11
msgid ""
"CPU Binding improves **host-side scheduling** for multi-socket ARM "
"servers with Ascend NPUs. It is designed to solve three common host-side "
"inference performance issues:"
msgstr "CPU 绑定改进了配备昇腾 NPU 的多插槽 ARM 服务器的**主机侧调度**。它旨在解决三个常见的主机侧推理性能问题："

#: ../../source/user_guide/feature_guide/cpu_binding.md:14
msgid ""
"**Lower cross-NUMA traffic.** Worker processes stay closer to the CPU and"
" memory resources selected for their active NPU, reducing remote NUMA "
"access."
msgstr "**降低跨 NUMA 流量。** Worker 进程更靠近为其活跃 NPU 选择的 CPU 和内存资源，从而减少远程 NUMA 访问。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/feature_guide/cpu_binding.md:16
msgid ""
"**Lower context-switch overhead from thread preemption.** Key runtime "
"threads run on stable CPU ranges, reducing scheduler movement and CPU "
"contention on busy hosts."
msgstr "**降低线程抢占导致的上下文切换开销。** 关键运行时线程在稳定的 CPU 范围内运行，减少调度器移动和繁忙主机上的 CPU 争用。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/feature_guide/cpu_binding.md:19
msgid ""
"**Better latency stability and multi-worker isolation.** Independent "
"workers avoid sharing the same CPU/NUMA resources, which helps reduce "
"tail-latency jitter and makes throughput more predictable during multi-"
"NPU serving."
msgstr ""
"**更好的延迟稳定性和多 Worker 隔离。** 独立的 Worker 避免共享相同的 CPU/NUMA 资源，这有助于减少尾延迟抖动，并使多 "
"NPU 服务期间的吞吐量更可预测。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/feature_guide/cpu_binding.md:23
msgid ""
"This feature is a host-side performance optimization. **It does not "
"change model execution logic or numerical outputs.** When memory "
"migration support is unavailable, CPU affinity still works, but memory "
"locality may be worse and latency or throughput may degrade."
msgstr ""
"此功能是主机侧的性能优化。**它不会改变模型执行逻辑或数值输出。** 当内存迁移支持不可用时，CPU "
"亲和性仍然有效，但内存局部性可能会变差，延迟或吞吐量可能会下降。"

